<HEADLINE> French Open Glance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- A look at Saturday's play in the French Open:  
</P>
<P>
	Attendance: 31,189 at Roland Garros stadium (31,495 in 1998).  
</P>
<P>
	Weather: Sunny with afternoon highs of 86 F.  
</P>
<P>
	Men's winners: Alex Corretja (6), Gustavo Kuerten (8) and Felix  
Mantilla (14). 
</P>
<P>
	Women's winners: Lindsay Davenport (2), Monica Seles (3), Steffi  
Graf (6) and Julie Halard Decugis (16). 
</P>
<P>
	Losers: Patrick Rafter (3) bowed to Fernando Meligeni.  
</P>
<P>
	On the women's side, Patty Schnyder (11) lost to Anna  
Kournikova. 
</P>
<P>
	Sunday's schedule: Carlos Moya (4)-Andre Agassi (13). Marcelo  
Rios (9)-Alberto Berasategui. Greg Rusedski(12)-Marcelo Filippini. 
</P>
<P>
	On the women's side, Martina Hingis (1)-Ruxandra Dragomir.  
Lindsay Davenport (2)-Jennifer Capriati, Monica Seles (3)-Julie 
Halard Decugis (16, Jana Novotna (4)-Sylvia Plitschke, Venus 
Williams (5)-Barbara Schwartz, Steffi Graf (6)-Anna Kournikova, and 
Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario (7)-Mary Joe Fernandez. 
</P>
<P>
	Quote: ``I guess that's the only way I can really talk is  
through my racket, because it's like any other thing I do or say, 
it always gets twisted around,'' Jennifer Capriati on not wanting 
to talk about her past personal problems. 
</P>
<P>
	Stat of the day: 45 tons- amount of crushed brick needed to  
maintain the courts during the French Open. 
</P>
</TEXT>
