<HEADLINE> Chorwon Wins Louisville Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Chorwon, with Calvin Borel aboard, closed  
from last on the turn and wore down Buff in the final strides to 
capture the $112,600 Louisville Handicap by a nose today at 
Churchill Downs. 
</P>
<P>
	Chorwon, the 6-year-old gelded son of Cozzene, has won the race  
three years in a row. 
</P>
<P>
	Chorwon covered the 1 3/8 miles in 2:14 and paid $4.40, $2.80 and  
$2.40 as the 6-5 favorite. Buff, ridden by Francisco Torres, took 
the lead at the top of the stretch before giving way and paid $4.60 
and $4. Keats and Yeats, a 20-1 outsider with Brian Peck aboard, 
finished another 1 1/4 lengths back in third and paid $5. 
</P>
<P>
	Chorwon won for the second time in six starts this year and  
increased his career earnings to $794,213. 
</P>
