	Swede Wins European Song Contest  
</P>
<P>
	JERUSALEM (AP) -- A Swedish singer won Europe's biggest song  
contest on Sunday in Jerusalem with a performance that was a 
throwback to the 1970s and the Swedish supergroup ABBA. Charlotte 
Nilsson, who won by singing ``Take Me To Your Heaven'' in a 
1970s-style pink-and-beige pantsuit, acknowledged the song mimicked 
the harmonies and chorus of the Swedish band. ``I guess it sounds a 
little like ABBA,'' she said at a news conference after the 
contest. It was Sweden's fourth win. 

</P>
