<HEADLINE> Holtz Won't Monitor Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBIA, S.C. (AP) -- South Carolina football coach Lou Holtz  
will turn down an invitation to help monitor elections in Indonesia 
so that he can attend Southeastern Conference meetings. 
</P>
<P>
	Holtz said he was selected by the State Department to serve as  
an official U.S. representative during the elections and that he 
was to leave Tuesday. The state department often selects 
politicians or community leaders to represent the United States at 
democratic elections in impoverished nations. 
</P>
