<HEADLINE> Son of Radio Host Sues District </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- The son of radio talk show host Art Bell sued a  
school district and a former substitute teacher who is serving a 
life prison sentence for sexually assaulting him. 
</P>
<P>
	Bell's son, Arthur Bell IV, is seeking unspecified damages in  
federal court, accusing the Nye County School District, its 
superintendent and a high school principal of negligently hiring, 
supervising and retaining former substitute teacher Brian Lepley. 
</P>
<P>
	The lawsuit also names Lepley, who was sentenced in May 1998 to  
life in prison for engaging in sexual acts with the younger Bell 
when he was a 16-year-old student and an 18-year-old man, the Las 
Vegas Review-Journal reported Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutors claimed Lepley, who is infected with the AIDS virus,  
supplied his victims with marijuana and alcohol on several 
occasions. 
</P>
<P>
	The suit was originally filed in November, a month after the  
teen's father suddenly announced he was quitting his radio program, 
a nationwide show with 15 million listeners that features theories 
from space aliens to CIA conspiracies. Bell had cited an 
unspecified ``threatening terrible event'' that occurred to his 
family. 
</P>
<P>
	Two weeks after quitting the airwaves on Oct. 13, Bell returned  
on Oct. 28 without explanation. 
</P>
<P>
	In an amended complaint filed Friday in Las Vegas, the younger  
Bell identified himself in the lawsuit, the newspaper said. 
</P>
<P>
	John Hawley, who represents Bell's son, and Bell have refused  
repeated requests for comment on the lawsuit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
