<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Feared Dead After Calif. Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Three Southern California Edison Corp.  
employees whose helicopter crashed in fog on their way to a 
business meeting on Catalina Island were missing and feared dead 
today. 
</P>
<P>
	The helicopter crashed Friday morning about three miles off  
Huntington Beach. The three were still missing when the search was 
suspended Friday night; rescuers were to resume the search today. 
</P>
<P>
	The helicopter left Irvine at about 6:30 a.m. and the pilot  
radioed 12 minutes later that he was over the ocean. No distress 
call or further transmission from the helicopter was received, said 
Coast Guard officials. 
</P>
<P>
	The body of a man was spotted from the air by rescuers four  
miles off the coast, but it went underwater and could not be 
retrieved, said Emiko Banfield, a spokeswoman for the utility 
company. 
</P>
<P>
	Crews from the Coast Guard and Huntington Beach Lifeguards  
searched with three ships and a helicopter for the woman and two 
men, whose identities were withheld. 
</P>
</TEXT>
