<DOCNO> APW19990529.0042 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-29 00:51:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> States, Sweepstakes Company Settle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Florida, Indiana, West Virginia and South  
Carolina: If you are one of the above lucky states, you are a 
winner of a share of $4 million! 
</P>
<P>
	American Family Publishers announced Friday that it had reached  
a $4 million settlement with these states, which had claimed the 
company used deceptive practices in its sweepstakes. 
</P>
<P>
	As part of the settlement, American Family agreed to stop  
telling people they are winners or members of a group of finalists 
unless that is actually the case. 
</P>
<P>
	Indiana Attorney General Jeffrey Modisett said the state's share  
of the money -- about $550,000 -- will partially reimburse hundreds 
of residents tricked by the company's mailings that often announce, 
``You are a winner'' in bold type. 
</P>
<P>
	``I can say we believe we have an adequate amount of money to  
make sure people who have been victimized will be compensated 
fairly,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The company, which admitted no wrongdoing in the deal, has been  
stung by news reports of elderly people who spent thousands of 
dollars to buy magazines they thought they had to purchase in order 
to collect prizes. 
</P>
<P>
	The problem was a big enough concern that several attorneys  
general from around the country met in February in Indianapolis to 
discuss strategy and hear from victims. 
</P>
<P>
	The Jersey City, N.J.-based company already had reached  
agreements with 35 other states and the District of Columbia. Iowa 
and Washington state still have complaints pending. 
</P>
<P>
	The exact amount consumers in each state will get will be  
determined later under a formula based on the number of American 
Family customers in each state. 
</P>
<P>
	Modisett also said American Family spokesmen Ed McMahon and Dick  
Clark have agreed to donate $10,000 to charity as part of the 
settlement. Both will send the money to the Muscular Dystrophy 
Foundation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
