<HEADLINE> Beach Boys Laud Tahoe Restrictions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INCLINE VILLAGE, Nev. (AP) -- Two members of the Beach Boys  
joined officials in welcoming new restrictions on most personal 
watercraft on Lake Tahoe. 
</P>
<P>
	``We want to be in the water. We want to have fun, fun, fun, but  
we don't want to pollute,'' said Bruce Johnson, who lives in Santa 
Barbara, Calif., on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Mike Love, a longtime resident of the Tahoe area, said a lot has  
changed since their band wrote songs about speeding cars and 
gas-guzzling behemoths in the old days. 
</P>
<P>
	``Now we're trying to do our part to help ... This is a step in  
evolution and a step to preserve one of the most beautiful places 
in the world,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	This Memorial Day weekend is the last time most Jet Ski  
enthusiasts can tear across Lake Tahoe. Effective Tuesday, most 
personal watercraft will be banned because of concerns about water 
pollution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
