<HEADLINE> Largent Into Wash. Hall of Fame </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- NFL Hall of Fame receiver Steve Largent, now a  
congressman from Oklahoma, heads a field of five new members 
inducted into the state of Washington Sports Hall of Fame. 
</P>
<P>
	Largent, who starred for the Seattle Seahawks from 1976-89,  
joined the late Rod Funseth, Rod Belcher, Pat Lesser Harbottle and 
Mac Wilkins. 
</P>
<P>
	Funseth won three events on the PGA tour, Harbottle is  
recognized as one of the state's all-time golf greats, Wilkins won 
a gold medal in the discus at the 1976 Olympics in Montreal and 
Belcher worked more than 50 years as one of the Northwest's top 
radio and TV sports broadcasters. 
</P>
<P>
	State of Washington Sports Hall of Fame member plaques are  
displayed in the State Historical Museum in Tacoma. 
</P>
