<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-29 19:11:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rangers Beat Celtic 1-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GLASGOW, Scotland (AP) -- The Glasgow Rangers defeated Old Firm  
rivals Celtic 1-0 Saturday on Rod Wallace's second-half goal to add 
the Scottish Cup to this season's league and League Cup titles. 
</P>
<P>
	Wallace got his 27th goal of the season after four minutes of  
the second half, scoring on a left-footed volley from five yards 
that got behind Celtic goalkeeper Jonathan Gould. 
</P>
<P>
	The match was played under tight security following a May 2 game  
between the two that the Rangers won 3-0 to take the league title. 
More than 100 fans were arrested and referee Hugh Dallas' head was 
gashed by a coin thrown from the stands. 
</P>
<P>
	This match went off without incident on the field with Dallas  
again in charge and swarms of disappointed Celtic fans leaving 
before the final whistle. 
</P>
<P>
	The most controversial play came in the 88th minute when Rangers  
captain Lorenzo Amoruso -- standing in the box -- was struck in the 
upper arm/shoulder area by a driving shot that was headed for the 
goal. Celtic players called for a penalty on a handball, but Dallas 
waved it off. 
</P>
<P>
	Playing for the fifth time this season after one victory each  
and two ties, both sides had a scoring chance in an evenly played 
first half before a sellout of 52,000 at newly refurbished Hampden 
Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Celtic's Paul Lambert hit the crossbar on a long volley in the  
21st minute and Wallace broke into the box all alone in the 27th 
only to lose control of the ball. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rangers, who have won the league title 10 of the last 11  
seasons, pulled off the same triple in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
	The Scottish Cup title was the Rangers' 28th, second to the 30  
won by Celtic. It was also the 13th time that Scotland's two most 
bitter rivals have met in this final with Celtic having won the 
previous three times. Celtic still leads 7-6 in those showdowns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
